&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Originally posted on &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/people/Corruption-Watch-Texas/61571888697510/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;Corruption Watch — Texas&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?id=61571888697510&amp;amp;story_fbid=pfbid02ER2GETZg1Qs7R1uqCdt2dQz35Jahsw9CxACm9fSiwEekfTm4kECigrHVJZSSWrGtl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;View original post&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>🔥 TOMORROW ON COFFEE WITH CORRUPTION WATCH 🔥 Before the headlines… Before the databases… Before Houston started offici...</title><link>https://aiether.info/corruption-watch/2026-05-27-tomorrow-on-coffee-with-corruption-watch-before-the-headline/</link><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 18:48:43 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://aiether.info/corruption-watch/2026-05-27-tomorrow-on-coffee-with-corruption-watch-before-the-headline/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;🔥 TOMORROW ON COFFEE WITH CORRUPTION WATCH 🔥 Before the headlines… Before the databases… Before Houston started officially tracking “Bodies on the Bayou”… There was Joe Campos Torres. In 1977, the body of a 23-year-old Vietnam veteran was recovered from Buffalo Bayou after a brutal encounter with Houston police — a case that helped ignite protests, riots, and decades of distrust. Tomorrow morning we begin tracing the timeline ALL the way back to the beginning: 📍 Buffalo Bayou 📍 “The Hole” 📍 The death that changed Houston history No conspiracies. This is historical investigation. ☕ Coffee With Corruption Watch 🕖 7:00 AM Central Thursday, May 28 #Houston #BodiesOnTheBayou #CoffeeWithCorruptionWatch #TexasHistory #BuffaloBayou #Accountability&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>